{"lemma":"ثَيِّبُ","slug":"ثَيِّبُ","root":"ث.#.ب","root_slug":"ث-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4284","n4803","n4807"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a man or woman who has ever been married; not a virgin","examples":[{"text":"تَائِبَاتٍ عَابِدَاتٍ سَائِحَاتٍ ثَيِّبَاتٍ وَأَبْكَارًا","english":"repentant, dedicated to worship and fasting—previously married or virgins."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a woman who is divorced or widowed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"some gramineous plant"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/θaj.jib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4284","headword_ar":"ثُيِبَ","root":"vA^b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", ('Eyn, T, M, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay^iba","text_ar":"ثَيِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKoot, L, and so in a copy of the A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaA^obN","text_ar":"ثَاْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaA^abN","text_ar":"ثَاَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became relaxed and sluggish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became affected with sluggishness and languor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvA='b","text_ar":"تثا=ءب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became affected with sluggishness and languor like the languor of drowsiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvA='b","text_ar":"تثا=ءب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvA^~b","text_ar":"تثاّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which last is approved by IDrd and Thábit Es-Sara- kustee, who disallow ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvA='b","text_ar":"تثا=ءب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", though this is the form commonly known and approved, and is the most chaste form: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or he became affected with languor like the heaviness of drowsiness, in consequence of something that he had eaten or drunk, without becoming insensible;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvA='b","text_ar":"تثا=ءب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or ↓ this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he yawned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened his mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of languor"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the heaviness of drowsiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he yawned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened his mouth, and stretched himself, on being affected by sluggishness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drowsiness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anxiety;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA, on the authority of IDrst;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he yawned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened his mouth, and emitted wind from his stomach, by reason of some affection thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA on the authority of EtTedmuree:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~avaAw^ubu","text_ar":"التَّثَاوُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uw^abaA='u","text_ar":"الثُّوَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, T, S, Mgh;) and is on the occasion of one's stretching himself, and being languid: (Lth, T:) one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavaAwaba","text_ar":"تَثَاوَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, T, S, O, Mgh;) [for] this is vulgar. (Msb.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadukumo faloyugaT~i","text_ar":"اَحَدُكُمْ فَلْيُغَطِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA tavaA^a'aba","text_ar":"اـِذَا تَثَاَءَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAhu","text_ar":"فَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When any one of you yawns, he should cover his mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the back of his left hand; for it is believed that the devil leaps into the uncovered yawning mouth]. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","M","A","TA","L","Mgh","Msb","Lth","T"]},{"entry_id":"n4803","headword_ar":"ثِيبٌ","root":"vwb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAy^ibN","text_ar":"ثَايِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4807","headword_ar":"ثَيِّبٌ","root":"vwb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawiybN","text_ar":"ثَوِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vayowibN","text_ar":"ثَيْوِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e.] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEilN","text_ar":"فَيْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who has become separated from her husband"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, Mgh, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman whose husband has died,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has been divorced, and has then returned to the marriage-state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is not a virgin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman to whom a man has gone in;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who has gone in to a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, ISk, S, Mgh, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person who has married:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, M, Msb;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikorN","text_ar":"بِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~imN","text_ar":"اَيِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAba","text_ar":"ثَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAth, Mgh, Msb;) because they generally return time after time to the marriage-state: (Mgh:) but mostly applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because she returns to her family in a manner different from the first [state]; (Msb;) or because the suitors return to her time after time: (Mgh:) or it is not applied to a man (Lth, El-'Eyn, T, M, Mgh, K) except in the dual form, as when one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladu Alv~ay~ibayoni","text_ar":"وَلَدُ الثَّيِّبَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, El-'Eyn, T, M, K:) and a woman is also termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvay~ibN","text_ar":"مُثَيِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvay~abN","text_ar":"مُثَيَّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaZamN","text_ar":"مُعَظَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [but see 2, last sentence but two:]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vayibN","text_ar":"ثَيِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~ibaAtN","text_ar":"ثَيِّبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mgh, Msb,) and the post-classical writers say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuy~abN","text_ar":"ثُيَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has not been heard as genuine Arabic: (Mgh, * Msb:) its pl. if applied to a man is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuy~ibuwna","text_ar":"ثُيِّبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~ay~ibaAni yurojamaAni waAlbikoraAni yujoladaAni wayugar~abaAni","text_ar":"الثَّيِّبَانِ يُرْجَمَانِ وَالبِكْرَانِ يُجْلَدَانِ وَيُغَرَّبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two persons of whom each has previously had carnal intercourse in marriage with one of the other sex shall be stoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"if they commit adultery together;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the two who have previously had no connubial intercourse with others shall be flogged and banished"},{"kind":"text","text":"if they commit fornication together]. (T.) ―         -b2-  It is also applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who has attained the age of puberty, though a a virgin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"tropically, and by extension of its proper signification. (IAth, TA.) ―         -b3-  This word is mentioned in the K [and M] in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vyb","text_ar":"ثيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its mention in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vwb","text_ar":"ثوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by the author of the K to be wrong: but IAth and many others decisively assert that it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAba","text_ar":"ثَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yavuwbu","text_ar":"يَثُوبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ he returned. ” (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Lth","T","M","K","AHeyth","TA","IAth","Ks","ISk","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}